# Chat Handoff (Always)

## Source of truth for next chat

**`docs/knowledge/15_MEMORY/Current-Context.md`** — agents already load this after Home every chat. That is the handoff. Do **not** paste a long handoff pack in chat unless the user explicitly asks for `handoff` / `new chat context`.

Optional archive note: `docs/knowledge/15_MEMORY/Handoff-Latest.md` — only if user asks for a copy-paste pack. Not required for switch.

## When to tell user: switch to a new chat

Proactively fire the **visible SWITCH CHAT banner** when any of these hit:

1. **Topic change** — new feature/bug unrelated to current thread
2. **Milestone done** — feature/fix/docs unit finished; next work is different
3. **Context bloat** — long thread (~15+ back-and-forth) or replies get repetitive/confused
4. **Agent drift** — wrong architecture, forgotten vault rules, or re-asking solved facts
5. **After big vault/rule change** — Brain OS / always-on rules updated; fresh chat loads rules clean
6. **User asks** — “switch chat” / “new chat”

Do **not** nag every turn. Once per trigger. Prefer switch over stuffing more into a dying thread.

## Visible banner (mandatory format)

When telling the user to switch, print **exactly this shape** — do not bury it in a paragraph:

```text
🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨
🔴 SWITCH CHAT NOW 🔴
🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨🚨
```

Then **one short reason line** (why). Example: `Milestone shipped · thread fat · Context.md updated.`

## Before SWITCH CHAT

1. Update `docs/knowledge/15_MEMORY/Current-Context.md` (Today / Next / Touch) — **required**
2. Do **not** dump a handoff fenced block unless user asked for handoff text
3. Point user: new chat reads Home → Current-Context automatically

## If user asks for handoff text

Only then write `Handoff-Latest.md` + paste a short copy-ready block (≤40 lines, no secrets, paths only). Same constraints as always (vault-first, palette, `/m` capture-only, no auth/schema/commit unless asked).
